    "Title": "Quantum",
    "Author": "Ciran Hilaris",
    "CoverImage": "",
    "Description": "Quantum refers to the smallest discrete unit of any physical property, such as energy, charge, or angular momentum, that can exist independently in an interaction.\r\nScientific Definition\r\nIn physics, a quantum (plural: quanta) is the minimum amount of a physical entity involved in an interaction. This concept, known as quantization, means that certain properties, like energy, cannot vary continuously but exist in discrete, indivisible amounts. For example, a photon is a single quantum of light.",
